    "competition": "Auto wash only - no other services visible on-site.\n   \nMinimal direct competition at this location.",
    "assessment_notes": "SITE ASSESSMENT (Feb 2, 2026):\n\nMOUNIR'S ASSESSMENT:\n> \"Only the auto wash is available for rent. There isn't even a vacuum bay. Location is 3/5. We are a couple of kilometers away from the industrial area, or fully industrial area. However the site would require us to build. Maybe it can be reformatted from the side to operate as a service bay. Overall in comparison to the others I would give it a 3/5 and rate it as possible.\"\n\nAVAILABLE FOR RENT (VERY LIMITED):\n- Auto wash only\n- NO vacuum bay\n- Would require building/construction\n\nPOTENTIAL OPPORTUNITY:\nCould potentially be reformatted/retrofitted from the side to operate as a service bay\n→ This would require investment and construction\n\nLOCATION:\n- Couple kilometers away from heavy industrial area\n- Better than SS575/SS582/SS799 (which were in/adjacent to industrial)\n- Residential area setting (villa-style buildings visible)\n- Trees and greenery\n\nPOSITIVES:\n- Large, open forecourt space\n- Residential demographics (better than industrial)\n- Clean, organized layout\n- Distance from heavy industrial zone\n- First Sharjah site rated above 2.5!\n\nNEGATIVES:\n- Only auto wash available (most limited scope yet)\n- No vacuum bay even\n- Would require construction/retrofit for service bays\n- Investment needed beyond rental\n\nCOMPARISON TO OTHER SITES:\nBetter location demographics than SS575/SS582/SS799, but even more limited scope (auto wash only vs. wash + vacuum).\n\nHowever, potential exists if site can be reformatted for service operations.\n\nVISUAL OBSERVATIONS (2 photos + 1 video):\n- Large forecourt with trees\n- Standalone auto wash structure\n- Residential area (villas visible)\n- Convenience store on-site\n- Spacious, organized layout\n\nRating: 3.0/5\nRecommendation: MAYBE (first non-No Go site!)\n\nRATIONALE FOR \"MAYBE\":\nBetter demographics than other Sharjah sites + potential for retrofit makes this worth keeping as an option if primary sites don't work out. Not shortlist-worthy due to limited current scope and construction requirements, but \"possible\" as Mounir noted.",
    "recommendation": "MAYBE",
    "recommendation_tag": "MAYBE",
    "status": "Assessed",
    "visit_date": "2026-02-02",
    "population_data": "Sharjah city population: 1.6 million (2022 Census), emirate total 1.8 million. 22% growth from 1.4M in 2015 to 1.8M in 2022. Metro area reached 1,872,000 in 2024. Al Manakh is part of Al Gharb district (western Sharjah), one of the densest mixed-use commercial/residential zones. Expat population: 1.6M (1.1M male, 500K female); Emirati citizens: 208,000. Sources: Sharjah Census 2022 via Gulf News (https://gulfnews.com/uae/sharjah-census-2022-results-out-emirates-population-reaches-18-million-1.95978023), MacroTrends (https://www.macrotrends.net/global-metrics/cities/22637/sharjah/population), The National (https://www.thenationalnews.com/uae/government/2023/05/24/sharjah-census-reveals-population-grew-22-per-cent-in-eight-years/)",
    "traffic_data": "Sharjah average congestion level: 50.1% (2025), up 2.4pp from 2024. Average speed during rush hour: 25.3 km/h. A 10km drive takes 19 min 40 sec on average. Al Manakh sits between E11 (Sheikh Zayed Road) and E311 (Sheikh Mohammed Bin Zayed Road), both major arterials. 90% of Dubai-Sharjah commuters report daily traffic jams. Commuters lose ~460 hours/year (~60 working days) in Dubai-Sharjah gridlock. Al Manakh industrial area generates heavy commercial vehicle traffic. Sources: TomTom Traffic Index Sharjah (https://www.tomtom.com/traffic-index/sharjah-traffic), Khaleej Times (https://www.khaleejtimes.com/uae/traffic-jams-dubai-sharjah), Gulf News (https://gulfnews.com/uae/90-of-dubai-sharjah-commuters-hit-by-traffic-jams-new-study-finds-1.500181486)",
    "competitors": "ADNOC is the sole retail fuel operator in Sharjah (78 stations emirate-wide). ENOC station 1177 located in Industrial Area 4, Sharjah Industrial Area (24hr, offers Special 95, Super 98, Diesel). Emarat station E7050 Mughaider in Industrial Area 12 (24hr). Multiple auto service competitors in the industrial zone: Sand Dance Tyre (industrial area), Dhanya Auto Care Center, Rukn Al Rayan Auto Tyres. CAFU on-demand fuel delivery also operates in Sharjah. Sources: 2GIS - ENOC 1177 (https://2gis.ae/sharjah/firm/70000001067369641), 2GIS - Emarat E7050 (https://2gis.ae/sharjah/firm/70000001044049888), XMAP ADNOC analysis (https://www.xmap.ai/blog/how-many-adnoc-service-stations-are-in-the-uae)",
    "infrastructure": "Major infrastructure investment: Sharjah's 2025 budget allocates 41% to infrastructure (7% rise from 2024). Asphalt reinstatement works at Al Manakh Area completed by Al Marwan Group. Service roads, parking, and footpaths developed for Sharjah Municipality at Manakh Area. Internal roads in Al Manakh, Musalla and other areas upgraded with mosque car park at Nasserya. Nearby: Industrial Area 6 infrastructure project includes 19km of new internal roads, modernized utility networks (water, gas, electricity, telecom). Al Nahda area (formerly Industrial Area 1) being converted to mixed-use investment/residential/commercial zone. Sources: Al Marwan Group (https://almarwangroup.com/projects/completed-roads-infrastructure-projects/), Zawya - Industrial Area 6 (https://www.zawya.com/en/economy/gcc/sharjah-unveils-updates-on-industrial-area-6-infrastructure-development-project-ikxn8167), JobXDubai - 2025 Budget (https://blog.jobxdubai.com/2024/12/24/sharjah-2025-budget-infrastructure-investment/)",
    "commercial": "Oasis Mall: ~5 min drive from Al Manakh (3 floors, 45+ retail stores, Carrefour Market, 10-screen cinema, 575-seat food court). Mega Mall: ~8 min drive (4 floors, entertainment, shopping). Sharjah Shopping Centre on Al Arouba Street nearby. Al Ghuwair Centre, K.M Trading, Rolla Mall also accessible. Carrefour and Talal Hypermarket serve as local supermarkets. Mixed-use properties in Al Manakh combine offices, retail (ground level), and residential (upper floors). Sources: Bayut Al Manakh Area Guide (https://www.bayut.com/area-guides/al-manakh/), Square Yards (https://www.squareyards.ae/area-guide/sharjah/al-manakh)",
    "transport": "Bus routes E303, E307, E307A, and E400 pass close to Al Manakh. Route 3: Rolla Square Park through Al Wahda Road to Industrial Areas (6:05am-10:05pm weekdays). Route 14: Al Jubail Bus Station to Al Sharq, Industrial Area 1 and Sharjah Airport. Highway access: E11 (Sheikh Zayed Road) and E311 (SMBZ Road) both accessible. Sharjah International Airport: ~13km east-southeast of central Sharjah. No metro in Sharjah; public transport via MOWASALAT bus system and taxis. Sources: Bayut Public Transport Guide (https://www.bayut.com/mybayut/public-transport-sharjah-guide/), Edarabia Bus Routes (https://www.edarabia.com/sharjah-bus-routes-map-timing-guide/), Sharjah Airport Wikipedia (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sharjah_International_Airport)",
