    "assessment_notes": "SITE ASSESSMENT (Feb 2, 2026):\n\nMOUNIR'S ASSESSMENT:\n> \"This site is in a slightly better neighborhood; however, it is literally one block, less than one kilometer away from the heavy industrial areas, similar to other Sharjah sites. Only the auto wash and vacuum bay are available for rent, with a Bridgestone tire repair in the middle and an ADNOC lube in the middle. This eliminates the ability to have a quick service center because of the layout so it can only be used as a car wash. Overall: 2.5/5.\"\n\nAVAILABLE FOR RENT (LIMITED):\n- Auto wash only\n- Vacuum bay only\n(NOT full service bays)\n\nEXISTING FACILITIES BLOCKING LAYOUT:\n- Bridgestone tire repair (middle bay)\n- ADNOC Lube (middle bay)\n→ Layout configuration eliminates ability to operate full quick service center\n\nLOCATION:\n- Slightly better neighborhood than SS575/SS582\n- BUT: Less than 1km from heavy industrial areas\n- Similar demographic issues to other Sharjah sites\n\nCRITICAL ISSUE:\nLayout does not support quick service operation - can ONLY be used as car wash. This is a fundamental limitation beyond just scope.\n\nPOSITIVES:\n- Clean, modern presentation\n- Organized layout\n- Bridgestone brand presence indicates decent traffic\n\nNEGATIVES:\n- Only car wash/vacuum available (NOT full ExpressFit opportunity)\n- Layout physically prevents quick service conversion\n- Proximity to industrial areas (<1km)\n- Limited scope\n\nDECISION RATIONALE:\nEven though slightly better than previous Sharjah sites, the combination of car wash-only scope and proximity to industrial areas makes this unsuitable. Layout configuration is a deal-breaker for quick service model.\n\nRating: 2.5/5\nRecommendation: No Go",
