    "competition": "NO ACTIVE COMPETITION - Zeez Workshop SHUT DOWN\n\nZEEZ HISTORY (from forecourt manager):\n- Operated for only 6 months\n- SHUT DOWN by municipalities\n- Reason: Did not have correct licenses\n- Tried to operate car wash between two buildings (licensing issue)\n\nCURRENT STATUS:\n- Workshop is closed/abandoned\n- KFC has rented the store room under \"oil change\" and \"battery\" area\n- No active quick service competitor on-site",
    "assessment_notes": "SITE ASSESSMENT (Feb 2, 2026):\n\nMOUNIR'S ASSESSMENT:\n> \"Zees is shut down, clearly from the pictures. Speaking to one of the forecourt managers, he told me that Zees was operational here for six months and then they were shut down basically because municipalities, they didn't have the correct licenses. Something like they tried to operate a car wash between the two buildings. He also told me that now KFC has rented the store room under where it says 'oil change' and 'battery', right next to the pit, is available for rent. I will assume that this office on the right where it says 'brake pad' and 'tire' is also for rent but that is not highlighted in a drawing in yellow. Overall location 2.5/5; there is some residential behind and across from the petrol station. Accessibility is 2.5/5 also.\"\n\nZEEZ WORKSHOP - CLOSED (Important Context):\n- Previously offered: Oil change, Battery, Brake pads, Tyre, AC service, Mechanical work, Auto electric work\n- Operational period: 6 months only\n- SHUT DOWN by municipalities\n- Reason: Did not have correct licenses (tried to operate car wash between two buildings)\n- Serves as cautionary tale: Licensing is critical\n\nCURRENT STATUS:\n- Zeez workshop is shut down/abandoned\n- KFC has rented store room under \"oil change\" and \"battery\" area\n- Equipment/signage still visible but not operational\n\nAVAILABLE FOR RENT:\nCONFIRMED:\n- Space next to the pit (under \"oil change\" and \"battery\" signage)\n\nASSUMED (not confirmed):\n- Office on the right (where \"brake pad\" and \"tire\" signage is)\n- Not highlighted in yellow on drawing, so uncertain\n\nLOCATION:\n- Some residential behind the petrol station\n- Some residential across from the petrol station\n- Better than pure industrial (SS575/SS582) but not as good as SS179\n- Rating: 2.5/5\n\nACCESSIBILITY:\n- Rating: 2.5/5\n\nLICENSING WARNING:\nZeez's failure due to licensing issues (operating car wash between buildings) is a critical lesson. Any development here must ensure:\n1. Proper municipal licenses secured BEFORE operations\n2. No creative interpretation of permitted uses\n3. All construction/layout approved by authorities\n\nPOSITIVES:\n- No active competition (Zeez is closed)\n- Some residential demographics\n- Space available for rent\n\nNEGATIVES:\n- Zeez failure shows potential licensing complications at this site\n- KFC already renting part of the space (reduces available area)\n- Only 2.5 ratings for location and accessibility\n- Unclear exactly what space is available\n\nVISUAL OBSERVATIONS (3 photos + 2 videos):\n- Zeez signage still visible but clearly not operational\n- Multiple service bays structure visible\n- \"Oil change\", \"Battery\", \"Brake pad\", \"Tyre\" signage areas\n- Site appears abandoned/inactive\n\nRating: 2.5/5\nRecommendation: No Go (TBD based on final assessment)\n\nRATIONALE:\nWhile there's no active competition (Zeez closed), the 2.5 ratings for location and accessibility, plus the cautionary tale of Zeez's licensing failure, suggest this site has challenges. The fact that Zeez couldn't make it work (even for 6 months) due to regulatory issues is a red flag.",
    "recommendation": "No Go",
    "recommendation_tag": "NO GO",
