    "traffic_rating": 2.5,
    "competition": "ADNOC LUBE in middle - NOT available for rent\n\nCompetition assessment: Minimal external competition visible.\n\nLAYOUT ISSUE: ADNOC Lube positioned in middle creates access/flow problem (similar to SS799 Bridgestone issue).",
    "assessment_notes": "SITE ASSESSMENT (Feb 2, 2026):\n\nMOUNIR'S ASSESSMENT:\n> \"So this site is Emirates Road. The auto wash, manual wash, and vacuum bay are available for rent. There's the ADNOC Lube in the middle that is not available for rent. The entrance to the service station, as you can see in the video, is off of the highway somewhat and then it splits into a service road and then you enter into the service station. I would give that a 2.5/5. The physical location: I'll give 3.5/5 in terms of the building itself but having the ADNOC Lube in the middle, obviously, is an issue. The surrounding area: I would give it a 2.5/5. I cannot tell what this yellow service center behind the gas station is; that's all.\"\n\nAVAILABLE FOR RENT:\n✓ Auto wash\n✓ Manual wash\n✓ Vacuum bay\n\nNOT AVAILABLE:\n✗ ADNOC Lube (in the middle) - THIS IS THE ISSUE\n\nLAYOUT PROBLEM:\nADNOC Lube positioned in the middle creates access/flow issue, similar to SS799's Bridgestone/ADNOC Lube blocking layout problem. Having the lube shop in the center disrupts optimal service bay flow.\n\nACCESSIBILITY (2.5/5):\n- Off highway\n- Splits into service road\n- Then enter service station\n- Multi-step access reduces convenience\n\nPHYSICAL BUILDING (3.5/5):\n- Modern facility\n- Good condition\n- Well-maintained\n- Clean layout\n\nSURROUNDING AREA (2.5/5):\n- Warehouses and industrial area behind the gas station\n- Industrial/warehouse zone\n- Not residential (highway + industrial location)\n- Industrial demographics not ideal for quick service\n\nLOCATION CHARACTERISTICS:\n- Highway location (Emirates Road)\n- Warehouses and industrial area behind station\n- Not residential\n- Service road access required\n- Industrial/highway corridor - poor demographics for retail quick service\n\nPOSITIVES:\n- Modern, well-maintained facility (best visual quality of Sharjah sites so far)\n- Vacuum bay available (better than SS179)\n- Auto + manual wash available\n- Clean, organized appearance\n\nNEGATIVES:\n- ADNOC Lube in middle blocks optimal layout\n- Highway access complexity (2.5 accessibility)\n- Surrounding area unclear/industrial (2.5 location)\n- Multi-step entry (highway → service road → station)\n\nCOMPARISON TO OTHER SITES:\n- Better facility quality than SS575/SS582/SS828\n- But layout issue similar to SS799 (something in middle blocking optimal flow)\n- Better than SS179 (has vacuum bay), but SS179 had better demographics (residential)\n\nVISUAL OBSERVATIONS (3 photos + 4 videos):\n- Modern ADNOC facility with professional appearance\n- ADNOC Lube, Manual Wash, Auto Wash, Vacuum Bay all visible\n- Multiple service bays\n- Clean forecourt\n\nRating: 2.5/5\nRecommendation: No Go\n\nRATIONALE FOR No Go:\nDespite modern appearance and good building quality (3.5), the layout issue (ADNOC Lube in middle), highway access complexity (2.5), and unclear surrounding area (2.5) make this site challenging. The \"something in the middle\" blocking optimal layout is a repeat pattern from SS799 and a significant operational concern.",
    "recommendation": "No Go",
    "recommendation_tag": "NO GO",
    "status": "Assessed",
    "visit_date": "2026-02-02",
    "population_data": "Sharjah city: 1.6 million (2022 Census). Metro area: 1,872,000 (2024). Station is in Sharjah Industrial Area 11, a commercial district bound by Maliha Road and Sheikh Mohammed Bin Zayed Road (E311). Mixed-use zone with residential apartments, shops, and warehouses. District 11 mega-development project: 3M+ sqft commercial destination being built adjacent. Sources: Gulf News Census (https://gulfnews.com/uae/sharjah-census-2022-results-out-emirates-population-reaches-18-million-1.95978023), Bayut Industrial Area 11 (https://www.bayut.com/area-guides/industrial-area-11/), Yahoo Finance District 11 (https://finance.yahoo.com/news/district-11-uaes-premier-business-122500389.html)",
    "traffic_data": "ADNOC station Emirates Road 761 at 365/1 Sheikh Mohammed Bin Zayed Road (E311). E311 is a major highway connecting all seven Emirates; regularly experiences heavy congestion during weekday peaks. Southbound (Sharjah to Dubai) severe congestion 06:30-09:00. Truck restrictions on E311: morning 06:30-08:30, afternoon 13:00-15:00, evening 17:30-20:00 (since April 2024). Emirates Road Enhancement Project (Sep 2025, 2-year duration): expanding from 3 to 5 lanes over 25km stretch, boosting capacity 65% from 5,400 to 9,000 vehicles/hour per direction. Station tends to be crowded during peak times with difficult entry/exit. Sources: 2GIS ADNOC 761 (https://2gis.ae/sharjah/firm/70000001019677263), UAE Edge E311 Guide (https://uaeedge.com/sheikh-mohammed-bin-zayed-road-complete-guide/), MOEI Emirates Road project (https://www.moei.gov.ae/en/media-center/news/15/7/2025/ministry-of-energy-and-infrastructure-launches-strategic-project-to-develop-emirates-road), RTA truck timing (https://www.rta.ae/wps/portal/rta/ae/home/news-and-media/all-news/NewsDetails/adjusting-truck-movement-timings-on-sheikh-mohammed-bin-zayed-road)",
    "competitors": "ADNOC station Emirates Road 761: 24hr, Special 95, Super 98, Lube, Car Wash, Car Sanitization, ATM, WC, Prayer Room. ADNOC Lube on-site creating access issues. ADNOC is sole retail fuel operator in Sharjah (78 stations). ENOC expanding aggressively: 28 stations in Sharjah (2025), UAE total 204. ENOC compact station on Al Kalba Road (10th compact station in UAE). ENOC stations in Muweilah (3,600 sqm, 8 dispensers) and Al Azra (2,508 sqm). Emarat station E7050 in Industrial Area 12. Sources: 2GIS ADNOC 761 (https://2gis.ae/sharjah/firm/70000001019677263), Waze ADNOC 761 (https://www.waze.com/live-map/directions/adnoc-service-station-or-emirates-road-(761)-e311-sheikh-mohammad-bin-zayed-road-sharjah-industrial-area-11?to=place.w.36307197.363268577.143341), Gulf News ENOC expansion (https://gulfnews.com/business/retail/enoc-adds-new-sharjah-fuel-station-bringing-uae-total-to-204-1.500223109)",
    "infrastructure": "District 11: Major commercial development on E311, spanning 3M+ sqft. 5 min from Sharjah International Airport and University City. Adjacent to Al Zahia City Centre and Al Zahia residential community. Emirates Road Enhancement Project (2025-2027): 3 to 5 lanes, 25km stretch, 6 directional bridges (12.6km total length, 13,200 vehicles/hour capacity). Aljada megaproject in nearby Muwaileh: 24M sqft, 25,000 homes, 7,600+ completed, population now 20,000+. Sources: Yahoo Finance District 11 (https://finance.yahoo.com/news/district-11-uaes-premier-business-122500389.html), MOEI Emirates Road (https://www.moei.gov.ae/en/media-center/news/15/7/2025/ministry-of-energy-and-infrastructure-launches-strategic-project-to-develop-emirates-road), Arada - Aljada (https://www.arada.com/en/latest-news/arada-completes-another-120-homes-at-sharjah-megaproject-aljada/)",
    "commercial": "Sharjah Industrial Area 11: commercial/industrial mixed-use district with trading companies and factories. District 11 development: new premier business hub under construction. Al Zahia City Centre nearby. Safari Mall accessible from industrial area roads. Sources: Bayut Industrial Area 11 (https://www.bayut.com/area-guides/industrial-area-11/), Yahoo Finance District 11 (https://finance.yahoo.com/news/district-11-uaes-premier-business-122500389.html)",
    "transport": "Direct access from Sheikh Mohammed Bin Zayed Road (E311) - major UAE highway. E311 connects Abu Dhabi to Ras Al Khaimah (~220km). 5 min from Sharjah International Airport. Near University City. Bus routes serving industrial areas available. Truck movement restricted during peak hours on E311 (since April 2024). Sources: Wikipedia E311 (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E_311_road_(United_Arab_Emirates)), UAE Edge E311 (https://uaeedge.com/sheikh-mohammed-bin-zayed-road-complete-guide/), 2GIS ADNOC 761 (https://2gis.ae/sharjah/firm/70000001019677263)",
